5. FLOOD FILL-LeetCode 733

Replace all connected cells that have the same color as the starting cell
with a new color.
Example:
    Original image:          Starting cell: (1, 1)    New color: 2
    1 1 1                    Output:
    1 1 0                    2 2 2
    1 0 1                    2 2 0
                             2 0 1
--------------------------------------------------
Idea:
    DFS from (sr, sc).
    Replace all cells with original color → new color.
    Stop when out of bounds or cell color != original.
--------------------------------------------------
Code:
def floodFill(image, sr, sc, color):
    original = image[sr][sc]
    if original == color:    # no change needed
        return image
    rows = len(image)
    cols = len(image[0])
    def dfs(r, c):
        if (
            r < 0 or
            c < 0 or
            r >= rows or
            c >= cols or
            image[r][c] != original
        ):
            return
        image[r][c] = color
        dfs(r + 1, c)
        dfs(r - 1, c)
        dfs(r, c + 1)
        dfs(r, c - 1)
    dfs(sr, sc)
    return image
--------------------------------------------------
Key Points:
    - Check if original == color first → avoids infinite recursion
    - Similar structure to Number of Islands but checks color instead of '1'/'0'
Time Complexity: O(rows x cols)
